Routing - frontend or SPA, navigation, path = "/posts" -> component 
path = "/posts/:postId" -> component with id


steps:
1. npx create-react-app demo-router
2. cd demo-router
3. npm install react-router-dom axios


Terminology
1. BrowserRouter - wraper of entire app routing
example - mysite.com/about
<BrowserRouter>
    <App />
  </BrowserRouter>
2. HashRouter - makes URL with hashtag
example - mysite.com/#about
3. Route - each individual route
4. Switch - group all routes together, top to bottom
	<Switch>
      <Route exact path="/" component= {HomePage} />
      <Route exact path="/:id" component= {UserPage} />
    </Switch>
5. Link - hyper link in routes
<p><Link to="/itasworkshop">itasworkshop</Link> on my GitHub</p>
